1) To use the PDQ library in C, go into /lib and:
- Select the Makefile closest to your platform
- make clean
- make

Check that libpdq.a has been produced.

---------------------------------------------
2) To use PyDQ, go into /python and:
- make clean
- make

Check that ./test.py runs.
If not:
- check that you have python installed.
- Check for unix pathing problems
- See http://www.perfdynamics.com/Tools/PDQcode.html#tth_sEc3.2

Some .py models examples use numerical routines from NumPy.
You may need to install NumPy on your platform.
Visit http://numpy.scipy.org/ for details.
